        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 4:23PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 423 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Windsor, or 7 miles southeast of Fort Collins, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Fort Collins, Greeley, northeastern Loveland,
Windsor, Johnstown, Milliken, Severance, Timnath, New Windsor
Reservoir and Kelim.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
